(2923, 1, '2026-04-17 16:30:37', '2026-04-17 16:30:37', 'Sydney Bernice Sweeney (born September 12, 1997) is an American actress. She gained early recognition for her roles in Everything Sucks!, The Handmaid\'s Tale and Sharp Objects in 2018. She received wider acclaim for her performances in the drama series Euphoria (2019–present) and the first season of the anthology series The White Lotus (2021), both of which earned her nominations for Primetime Emmy Awards.\n\nIn film, Sweeney garnered critical acclaim for her performances in the drama film Reality (2023) and for her portrayal of professional boxer Christy Martin in the biopic Christy (2025), and has also appeared in the box office hits Anyone but You (2023) and The Housemaid (2025). Her other film credits include Once Upon a Time in Hollywood (2019), Madame Web (2024), and Immaculate (2024).\n\nDescription above from the Wikipedia article Sydney Sweeney, licensed under CC-BY-SA, full list of contributors on Wikipedia.', 'Sydney Sweeney', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'sydney-sweeney', '', '', '2026-04-17 16:30:37', '2026-04-17 16:30:37', '', 0, 'http://localhost/jobsity/actors/sydney-sweeney/', 0, 'actor', '', 0),
